RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 1 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 76. Maiden Claiming Purse 19500. FOR MAIDENS, FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000 (Registered Florida Breds Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DELTA RIDGE raced in the three path around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, continued around the far turn still in the three path, began a bid passing the quarter pole and got up for the win late. ROYAL COURT bumped with the horses to both sides at the start, raced in the three path around the first turn, tracked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the far turn and in upper stretch and was caught in the final strides. J J'S JUSTICE saved ground around the first turn, led the way on the inside up the backstretch, dueled from the rail around the far bend and gave way in the final sixteenth. ANTHRACITE bumped with the horse to her inside at the start, recovered to press the pace while saving ground around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far turn and was outkicked in the lane. MAGNA RULER raced off the pace in the two path through the opening half mile, continued around the far bend still in the two path and never threatened. TEPPER bumped with the horse to his outside leaving the gate, raced in the two path early, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the outside, saved ground around the second turn and made no bid.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 2 7F Dirt CR: 97. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 19500. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $8,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $12,500. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 5 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since January 5 Allowed 4 lbs. Clai ming Price $12,500 (Races Where Entered For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SAN COSTANTINO raced off the pace on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the turn and kicked clear in the final furlong. KING CAIRO raced in the middle of the pack on the inside early, saved ground around the turn and chased the winner home in the lane. FLIPPING FISH raced in the middle of the pack on the outside early, began a bid from the two path coming around the bend and finished evenly. HIDE THE DEMON led the field on the inside up the backstretch, continued to show the way while saving ground around the turn and weakened in the final furlong. TONY SMALL chased the leader between horses up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the two path and faded in the stretch. LORD BARNA trailed the field throughout, raced in the three path around the turn and was not a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 3 1 1/16M Turf CR: 62. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Not Started For Less Than $16,000. The Same Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Started For Less Than $16,000 And Since Then Have Finished 2nd Or 3rd For $16,000 Or More.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COLLECTIVE GOLD hopped up and bumped mildly with the horse to her inside leaving the gate, raced in the two path around the first turn, settled off the pace on the inside for the run up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the four path, began a bid approaching the quarter pole and gained ground to get up for the win late. DUDEFOOLINGDARLING saved ground around the first turn, tracked the leaders on the inside up the backstretch, continued around the far bend in the two path and gained ground in late stretch. PEACE FIRE pressed the pace on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the second turn, led in upper stretch, was caught late and kept on to the wire. I LOVE IRELAND bumped lightly with the horse to her outside at the break, recovered to chase the leader on the outside through the opening half mile, began a bid from three path coming around the far turn, dueled in upper stretch and was outfinished late. HEAVEN'S D'ORO saved ground around the first turn, led the way on the inside up the backstretch, dueled from the rail around the second bend and weakened in late stretch. CAIRO WINNER saved ground early, raced in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, navigated the second bend from the four path and finished evenly. SISTER SAINT raced in the three path around the first turn, settled off the pace on the outside for the run up the backstretch, dropped back while saving ground around the far turn and made no bid. WINE WITH A ROSE raced in the two path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the outside, came around the far bend in the three path and faded in the lane. DAZZLING THE MOON trailed the field the entire way around the oval, saved ground throughout and was never a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 4 7F Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 13500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE SEPTEMBER 5. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHARGE IT JENN tracked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the turn, dueled in the lane in tight quarters and edged clear late. LADY TEUFLESBERG raced in the middle of the pack on the inside up the backstretch, began a bid from the four path coming around the turn, drifted in and brushed with CHARGE IT JENN in upper stretch and dueled to the wire from there to narrowly miss. FANCYSOUL dueled on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, led the way from the two path coming around the bend and dug in the lane, giving way in the final strides. MA MEATLOAF dueled on the inside early, raced in the four path around the turn and weakened in the lane. LOVIN LIVIN raced in the middle of the pack on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the five path and finished evenly. LYRICAL raced off the pace on the inside through the opening stages, swung out to the six path for the run around the bend and never threatened. MELANCHOLY BLUES raced off the pace on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the two path and made no bid. SNACKSTER was reluctant to load, broke sharply and dueled between horses up the backstretch, dropped back while saving ground around the turn and tired further in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 5 1 1/16M Turf CR: 57. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Not Started For Less Than $16,000. The Same Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Started For Less Than $16,000 And Since Then Have Finished 2nd Or 3rd For $16,000 Or More.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MARVELOUS LADY saved ground around the first turn, tracked the leader on the inside up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the second bend, launched a bid approaching the quarter pole and kicked clear in the lane. KHARKIV led the way while saving ground around the first turn and up the backstretch, dueled from the rail around the far turn, was caught in upper stretch and chased the winner home from there. CAYMAN QUEEN raced in the two path early, settled off the pace on the outside for the run up the backstretch, continued around the second turn in the three path, launched a bid approaching the quarter pole and gained ground late. EMPIRE GIRL saved ground around the first bend, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the inside, moved up while racing in the three path around the second turn, and improved position in the stretch but was outkicked late. REBATE raced in the middle of the pack in the three path through the opening half mile, began a bid from the two path coming around the far bend and flattened out in the lane. ROMANCE PELUSA raced in the two path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch off the pace on the inside, navigated the far turn from the four path and made no bid. VALIANT MISTRESS raced in the two path around the first bend, chased the leader on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the far turn still in the two path and tired entering the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 6 7F Dirt CR: 70. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 5 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since January 5 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000 (Races Where Entered For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Registered Florida Breds Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STARSHIP PRECIOUS raced in the middle of the pack up the backstretch, began a bid from the four path coming around the turn and gained ground in the stretch to get up for the win late. BELLA ROMANCE brushed lightly with the horse to her inside leaving the gate, recovered to press the pace on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, raced in the three path around the turn and dueled down the stretch, getting caught late. MORE MUCHO hopped up leaving the gate, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, began a bid from the five path coming around the bend and gained ground late. CHICAGO RIVER bumped with the horse to her inside at the break, dueled between horses up the backstretch, continued to battle from the two path around the turn and down the stretch and gave way in the final strides. MY GIRL MELLY bumped with the horse to her outside at the start, settled off the pace for the run up the backstretch, saved ground around the end and improved position mildly in the lane. LIL ANNIE ROSE dueled on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, continued to battle while saving ground around the turn and weakened in the lane. LEMON TAFFY trailed the field on the inside early, switched out the five path for the run around the turn and passed tiring horses in the lane. J'S STAR JET raced off the pace on the inside through the opening stages, saved ground around the bend and never threatened. BRASS BAND tracked the leaders on the inside up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the turn and tired in the stretch. A FOOLISH FANCY raced at the back of the pack on the outside in the early going, navigated the turn from the five path and made no bid. WIN OR CELLAR stalked the leaders on the outside in the opening stages, began to drop back while racing in the three and four path around the turn and continued to tire from there. DURA THE EXPLORER brushed mildly with the horse to her outside leaving the gate, raced in the middle of the pack up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the two path and faded in the stretch.

Claiming Price $16,000 (Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Not Started For Less Than $16,000. The Same Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Started For Less Than $16,000 And Sin ce Then Have Finished 2nd Or 3rd For $16,000 Or More.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DISTORTED TIMES raced in the two path around the first turn, chased the leader up the backstretch, challenged from the three path coming around the far turn and dueled to the wire to just hold the win. TAKEOVER KASH bumped with the horse to his outside leaving the gate, saved ground around the first bend, settled off the pace on the inside for the run up the backstretch, began a bid from the four path coming around the second turn and dueled to the finish, just missing. LORD OF THE NILE raced in the middle of the pack on the outside through the opening half mile, saved ground around the far bend and gained ground late while never threatening the top two. URBAN BEACH bumped with the horses to both sides at the start, trailed the field while saving ground around the first turn and up the backstretch, moved up while racing on the rail around the far bend and continued to improve position in the lane. TRAVEL GUIDE saved ground early, raced in the middle of the pack on the inside up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the two path and showed no kick. FROSTY WARRIOR was bumped hard and squeezed back leaving the gate, raced at the back of the pack on the inside through the opening half mile, swung out to the five path for the run around the second bend and never threatened. THE POINT ROAD raced in the three path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch off the pace on the outside, navigated the far turn from the four path and made no bid. MOTANAAFER raced at the back of the pack in the two path through the opening half mile, dropped back to trail the field while saving ground around the far turn and was empty from there. WILLWORKFORFOOD saved ground around the first turn, led the way up the backstretch, dueled from the rail around the far turn and tired quickly in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 8 6F Dirt CR: 79. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 5 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since January 5 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000 (Races Where Entered For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Al lowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KUHL STAR raced in the middle of the pack on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the four path coming around the turn, gained ground in the lane and kicked clear late. ALL FOOLS DAY bumped with the horse to his outside leaving the gate, recovered to lead the field up the backstretch, continued to show the way from the two path coming around turn, dug in in the lane and was caught late. JACKSON STRONG stumbled and bumped with the horse to his outside at the break, moved up to stalk the leaders in the early going, came around the turn in the three path and kept on to the finish. FREELANCE raced in the middle of the pack on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, continued around the bend in the two path and improved position in the lane. GOT EM THINKING raced off the pace up the backstretch, began to move up while racing in the five path around the turn and continued to improve position mildly in the stretch. THEJIGISUP raced at the back of the pack on the outside early, came around the bend in the three path and improved position mildly in the stretch while drifting significantly and never truly threatening. ANY MINUTE chased the leader on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the three path and faded in the lane. TEN MILES HIGH bumped with the horse to his inside and was forced back leaving the gate, recovered to track the pace setters on the inside up the backstretch, raced in the four path around the bend and tired from there. AS DE ORO COCO veered in and bumped with the horse to his inside at the start, settled in the middle of the pack between horses early, came around the turn in the three path and was empty in the stretch. BRONX chased the leader on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, saved ground around the bend and tired in the lane. JAMA DILLON raced at the back of the pack on the inside through the opening stages, navigated the bend from the four path, swung wide into the stretch and was never a factor.

Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since February 5 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since January 5 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Races Where Entered For $16,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Condition Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SIR SAFFER raced in the three path around the first turn, tracked the leaders on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the two path coming around the far turn, kicked clear in upper stretch and held that margin to the wire. THE SKIPSTER raced in the two path around the first turn, chased the leaders on the inside up the backstretch, continued around the far turn in the three path and gained ground in late stretch. ALYANAABI dueled on the inside around the firs turn and up the backstretch, saved ground around the second bend, could not go with the winner in the lane and chased that rival home. AIRMAN raced in the two path around the first turn, trailed the field on the inside up the backstretch, navigated the far bend from the two path, began a bid passing the quarter pole and gained ground late. HEREBY raced in the middle of the pack between horses through the opening half mile, continued around the second turn still in the three path and finished evenly. EXUMA (IRE) raced in the four path around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, came around the second turn in the three path and showed no kick. GAMBLING TZAR raced at the back of the pack on the outside through the opening half mile, navigated the far bend from the four path and never threatened. REBEL EMPIRE raced in the two path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the inside, came around the second bend still in the two path and weakened from there. SILENT SONATA saved ground early, raced off the pace up the backstretch, continued around the far turn in the four path and made no bid. CLEMSON TIGER raced in the three path around the first turn, dueled on the outside up the backstretch, dropped back while saving ground around the far turn and continued to tire from there.
